cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.NE 

This paper is about attacking machine learning based malware detection algorithms, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on recurrent neural networks (RNN), which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed algorithm involves training a substitute RNN to approximate the victim RNN, which could also relate to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of a generative RNN to output sequential adversarial examples suggests that it could also fall under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE).
